Dapchi school girls are released by the Boko Haram who kidnapped them on February 19, 2018. NTA correspondent, Hussaini Muhammed Isa who spoke with NTA Good Morning Nigeria Studio via phone call confirmed the release and said he was on his way from Damaturu to Dapchi town.  Details later. A.M Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. With a decade experience in Television journalism, and a graduate of University of Maiduguri. Tanimu also produces TV shows with NTA when not on Social media.